JD - 2:

Key Responsibilities:
- Lead and manage the production of VTOL platforms, ensuring adherence to timelines, cost, and quality standards.
- Develop and implement production strategies, processes, and best practices for efficient manufacturing.
- Coordinate with design, engineering, supply chain, and quality teams to ensure seamless integration of components.
- Drive continuous improvement initiatives to optimize production efficiency and reduce costs.
- Ensure compliance with aerospace industry standards, certifications, and regulatory requirements.
- Manage vendor relationships and oversee procurement of critical components.
- Monitor production KPIs and prepare regular reports for senior management.
- Mentor and develop a high-performing production team.

Required Qualifications & Skills:
- Education: B.Tech / M.Tech in Aerospace, Electronics & Communication (ECE), or Mechanical Engineering.
- Experience: 15+ years in aerospace or defense manufacturing, with at least 5 years in a leadership role.
- Proven expertise in VTOL or UAV production processes.
- Strong knowledge of lean manufacturing, Six Sigma, and quality management systems.
- Excellent leadership, communication, and stakeholder management skills.
- Familiarity with defense industry compliance and certification standards.

Preferred:
- Experience in composite materials and advanced manufacturing techniques.
- Exposure to defense projects and working with government agencies.

